parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to become stuck, making it impossible to use, which can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt is stuck in the retracted position
the seat belt is locked and cannot be pulled out
the seat belt is jammed
the seat belt retractor is faulty
the seat belt cannot be used.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the loss of power steering assist, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, especially at low speeds, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering system fails
the vehicle is difficult to steer
the power steering assist is lost
the steering wheel is hard to turn
the vehicle dies or stalls while driving
the vehicle will not restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the vehicle's electrical system to malfunction, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing the vehicle to stall or die, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle's electrical system malfunctions
the vehicle dies or stalls while driving
the vehicle will not restart
the battery is dead
the alternator belt fails
the alternator warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Cruise Control Vacuum Solenoid Valve Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control vacuum solenoid valve can cause the cruise control to malfunction, leading to unintended acceleration, which can result in accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The cruise control engages but cannot be disengaged
the vehicle accelerates unintentionally
the cruise control does not respond to driver input.
